##exploring a somewhat weighted endemism
#first, summing species occurrences
tmp <- apply(spp.grid, 2, sum)

#checking first ten values
tmp[1:10]
##   Aeschynomene americana      Aeschynomene bradei  Aeschynomene brasiliana 
##                      116                        1                       96 
##    Aeschynomene brevipes   Aeschynomene carvalhoi     Aeschynomene ciliata 
##                       47                        5                       27 
## Aeschynomene denticulata       Aeschynomene egena     Aeschynomene elegans 
##                       47                        1                       59 
##      Aeschynomene evenia 
##                       72
#then penalizing widespread species
spp.grid2 <- t(t(spp.grid)/tmp)

#(re)compute level of endemism
tmp <- apply(spp.grid2, 1, sum)
head(tmp)
##    Cell_75    Cell_76    Cell_77   Cell_131   Cell_134   Cell_137 
## 0.00862069 0.26204819 0.00862069 0.26367119 0.01388889 0.00862069
range(tmp)
## [1] 0.005050505 2.648131423
##finally rescale between 0 (lowest) and 1 (highest endemism).
w.endemism <- rescale(tmp, to = c(0, 1))
head(w.endemism)
##     Cell_75     Cell_76     Cell_77    Cell_131    Cell_134    Cell_137 
## 0.001350766 0.097234135 0.001350766 0.097848192 0.003343970 0.001350766

## [1] 0 1

###some boxplots
#ignoring outliers to improve visualizations (but kruskal test for all data)
#richness
ggplot(data = subset(spp.div, !is.na(Biome)), aes(x = Biome, y = spp.alpha)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = quantile(spp.div$spp.alpha, c(0.1, 0.9))) +
  theme(text = element_text(size=18),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size=15, angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(y = "Species Richness", x = '',
       subtitle = paste('p-value (Kruskal-Wallis) = ',
                        format(kruskal.test(spp.alpha ~ Biome,
                                            data = spp.div)$p.value, digits = 1)))

#weighted endemism
ggplot(data = subset(spp.div, !is.na(Biome)), aes(x = Biome, y = w.endemism)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = quantile(spp.div$w.endemism, c(0.1, 0.9))) +
  theme(text = element_text(size=18),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size=15, angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(y = "Weighted Endemism", x = '',
       subtitle = paste('p-value (Kruskal-Wallis) = ',
                        format(kruskal.test(w.endemism ~ Biome,
                                            data = spp.div)$p.value, digits = 1)))

##save data frames
write.table(spp.grid, 'spp_grid.csv', sep = ',')
write.table(spp.div, 'spp_div.csv', sep = ',')
